From: tawc
Origin: own

EGL Wayland: fall through to the swrast init's Kopper-Zink branch when
the DRM init fails and MESA_LOADER_DRIVER_OVERRIDE=zink is set.

On tawc-on-Android we have no `/dev/dri/...` exposed to the app uid —
Android won't allow it through SELinux — so `dri2_initialize_wayland_drm`
always fails (the DMA-BUF/wl_drm-driven device fd never resolves).
Mesa's existing fallback then sends us into `dri2_initialize_wayland_swrast`
with `Options.Zink=false`, which means `driver_name="swrast"` →
llvmpipe-via-swrast. We want `driver_name="zink"` → Kopper, which is
already a supported configuration in this same function (line ~3210:
`disp->Options.Zink ? "zink" : "swrast"`), it's just unreachable
because eglapi.c's retry logic resets `Options.Zink=false` before the
last-resort swrast call.

The Vulkan side of this path already works on device: native Vulkan
apps (vkcube, etc.) talk to libhybris's libvulkan directly via the
LIBHYBRIS_ZINK backend's `LD_LIBRARY_PATH` shadow, and libhybris's
WSI presents through `native_window_queueBuffer` →
`wl_surface.attach` with android_wlegl buffers. With this patch,
Zink rides the same Vulkan + WSI to translate GL → SPIR-V → AHB
presentation without ever touching `/dev/dri/` or dmabufs.

See notes/libhybris-zink.md for the surrounding design + why dmabufs
aren't viable on Android.

diff --git a/src/egl/drivers/dri2/platform_wayland.c b/src/egl/drivers/dri2/platform_wayland.c
index 59cfa753290..185d7424e8f 100644
--- a/src/egl/drivers/dri2/platform_wayland.c
+++ b/src/egl/drivers/dri2/platform_wayland.c
@@ -3253,8 +3253,22 @@ dri2_initialize_wayland(_EGLDisplay *disp)
 {
    if (disp->Options.ForceSoftware)
       return dri2_initialize_wayland_swrast(disp);
-   else
-      return dri2_initialize_wayland_drm(disp);
+   if (dri2_initialize_wayland_drm(disp))
+      return EGL_TRUE;
+   /* tawc-fork: with MESA_LOADER_DRIVER_OVERRIDE=zink, the DRM init
+    * may have failed simply because there is no /dev/dri/ on this
+    * system (tawc-on-Android). The swrast init already handles
+    * driver_name="zink" + Kopper for the no-KMS case; fall through
+    * to it instead of letting eglapi.c's retry reset Options.Zink.
+    * Force fd_render_gpu=-1 so dri2_create_screen passes -1 to
+    * driCreateNewScreen3 (Kopper takes the no-DRM path with -1; with
+    * the calloc default of 0 it would do DRM ioctls on stdin). Same
+    * trick `surfaceless_probe_device_sw` uses upstream. */
+   if (disp->Options.Zink) {
+      dri2_egl_display(disp)->fd_render_gpu = -1;
+      return dri2_initialize_wayland_swrast(disp);
+   }
+   return EGL_FALSE;
 }

 void
